Welcome to your next home in the sought-after Apalachee Falls neighborhood—a family-friendly, amenity-rich community known for its safety, abundant green space, mature trees, and peaceful charm. This inviting 3-bedroom, 2-bath home sits on a large yard with a back patio, offering a perfect blend of privacy and space for outdoor living.
Inside, the open floor plan creates a warm and spacious feel—ideal for both entertaining and everyday family life. The kitchen features granite countertops, a pantry, and generous counter space, while the living and dining areas flow seamlessly for easy hosting and connection. We’ve spent countless evenings gathered around the bar, sharing long conversations while cooking dinner.
The master suite is conveniently located just off the main living area, offering both privacy and accessibility so you can stay close to the rest of the family. Storage is plentiful, with extra closets throughout, a floored attic, and a two-car garage that has served us as both a gym and storage space.
Our large yard has been the backdrop for family soccer and volleyball games, while the back patio is perfect for morning coffee or evening wind-downs. This home truly shines with its stunning views—offering some of the best sunrises, sunsets, and rainbows you’ll find anywhere.
Located just 5 minutes from local elementary, middle, and high schools, and 10 minutes from grocery stores, Target, restaurants, and shopping, the home also boasts easy access to Hwy 316. You’re only 30 minutes from Athens and 45 minutes from Atlanta, making it the ideal spot for convenience with a small-town feel.
Our family of six has truly thrived in this home, and we know you will too. Don’t miss your chance to call this peaceful retreat in Apalachee Falls home
